com.lucidworks.fusion.connector.plugin.api.fetcher.type.content

Class Content

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.lucidworks.fusion.connector.plugin.api.fetcher.type.content.Content
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EmittedItem, Fields, Identifiable, Message, Metadata, OutputItem, java.io.Serializable

    public class Content
extends java.lang.Object
implements EmittedItem, Fields, Metadata
    Content types are items that will be sent to a Fetchers transform() method, which normally consumes the Content's InputStream and emits Documents. Content types are never emitted to the external controller, only the local Connector plugin (Fetcher.transform) deals with these types.
